choices.text:
not ISIS or other terrorist groups, or even the government- it's being deaf and dumb. I can't survive in Syria without a job in my early thirties because everything I do needs verbal communication, even driving. There's almost no car without radio that I can relate to. Some people never heard of ASL or even thought of people who cannot hear. I haven't yet found a job with a company that hires non-hearing people because I need it. I can't get a scholarship to go to school because I need to bring a doctor's certificate and they don't have at hospitals in my city. No one wants to hire me because it's hard to hire people with disability in Mayadin city. I'm sick of hearing people ask "what's wrong with your face" and "why aren't you talking?" The only ones I can communicate with are my family and older people who are often annoyed with asking me to repeat things. Do you know how hard it is to understand Syrian Arabic? (just joking, but it does get annoying when they ask you to repeat things and you already did and you're sure you said it clearly).

This is not about politics but about a disability that needs appropriate treatment. We need classes about interacting with people with disabilities, job opportunities for people with disabilities, and teachers of ASL (North Syrian sign langauge please!) Please help me and send your ideas. I'm not leaving the country, I won't abandon my family, but
